### Filling the gaps? Private sector response to the push and pull of the Indian public schooling system

**Kasturi Kandalam**, Prashant Dewan, Sabyasachi Dey, Arnab Mukhopadhyay, and Soham Sahoo

We investigate how the private education sector responds to changes in public school quality and availability across India. Using state-level policy variations and household survey data, we analyze the dynamics between public and private schooling and their implications for educational equity and access.

</div>

<div class="wip-entry">

### Who Knows Best? (Dis)agreement on Reported Participation of Women in Intra-Household Decision-Making

**Kasturi Kandalam** and Rosa Abraham

This research examines discrepancies between spouses' reports on women's participation in household decision-making using nationally representative data from India. We document systematic patterns of disagreement across different types of decisions and explore their determinants and implications for measuring women's empowerment.

</div>

